A 16-year-old boy is in a stable condition after suffering a medical condition at the Hillcrest swimming pool on Thursday. Emergency services spokesperson Russel Meiring told The New Age that the teenager is currently in a stable condition. &#8220;The boy is in a critical yet stable condition in Hospital, said Meiring. According to ER24 when paramedics arrived at the scene they found a medical student performing CPR on the 16-year-old boy. The paramedics then took over treatment and continued with CPR and advanced life support interventions until the patient s vital signs returned. The boy was pulled from the pool by members of the public who initiated treatment and CPR and the cause of the incident is unknown. &#8220;Unfortunately we do not know what caused the incident&#8221;, said Meiring.-TNA Reporter